      <note>NAME:
get_job_and_trans_directories

PART OF:
This job is part of export_repository_to_files. It is not meant to be run stand alone.

PURPOSE:
This job expects to be called for each row of the result of the previous job, 
which is supposed to send it a result set containing a directory name. 
The directory name is originally extracted from a repository export, 
and this job is responsible for creating the directory on the file system 
in order to store .ktr and .kjb files from the same repository export.

The job has to resign to a bit of a hack before it can actually create the directory.
The only way to parameterize the name of directory to create, the directory name 
must be set in a variable. 

Because the name of the directory arrives as a result from the calling job entry, 
we first need to call the transformation set_job_or_trans_dir_variable to grab to argument.
The transformation then sets that as the variable JOB_OR_TRANS_DIR. 
Beyond that point this job can take over and use the variable to create the directory. 

Ugly, but it works.</note>
